# Package list — full-file overlay over the upstream releng packages.x86_64.
# Re-diff against /usr/share/archiso/configs/releng/packages.x86_64 when
# bumping the archiso package, to pick up new upstream additions.
#
# Networking note: NetworkManager is the *only* enabled networking unit on
# the rescue ISO (see overlay/airootfs/etc/systemd/system/). dhcpcd, iwd,
# and wpa_supplicant are intentionally retained because:
#   - They are diagnostic / fallback CLI tools, not just daemons.
#   - In a recovery scenario where NetworkManager is broken or you need to
#     hand-bring an interface up, having them present (but not enabled) is
#     the difference between fixing a system and being stuck.
# They will not race NetworkManager because their .service units are not
# linked into multi-user.target.wants.
